## 💡 Key Concept: MinConfidence Threshold

```python
# Strict — only report high-confidence findings (fewer false positives)
MinConfidence=80

# Balanced — good for most use cases
MinConfidence=50

# Sensitive — catch everything, more false positives
MinConfidence=10
```

Adjusting `MinConfidence` is a core trade-off between **precision** (fewer false positives) and **recall** (catching more real issues). This is a frequently tested concept on the AIF-C01 exam.

